[normal]Written evidence submitted by [bold]BBC Watch[bold] [FBB[bold] [bold]0041][bold]Executive summary:[bold]a) The BBC consistently fails to meet its own Editorial Guidelines on accuracy and impartiality in its Middle East reporting, thus compromising its reputation as a trustworthy broadcaster.
[normal]b) Such editorial failures are increasingly apparent on social media which is in rising use by BBC employees.
[normal]c) The BBC consistently fails to meet its fifth public purpose with regard to its representation of the Arab-Israeli conflict and the Middle East peace process, failing to promote well-rounded audience understanding of these issues.
[normal]d) The current system of self-regulation and the over-complicated complaints system are considered unsustainable by members of the public. 
[normal]Introduction:[bold]BBC Watch (
[normal]http://bbcwatch.org/
[normal]) is an independent project of CAMERA (Committee for Accuracy in Middle East Reporting in America) which was established in October 2012 in order to monitor the BBC's coverage of Israel for accuracy and impartiality as defined by the BBC's own Editorial Guidelines. 
[normal]Since its establishment, BBC Watch has documented numerous breaches of those editorial guidelines and consistent failure to meet the terms of the fifth category of Public Purposes defined in the BBC's Charter 
[normal]During that time, BBC Watch has also been contacted by many members of the public with regard to the unsatisfactory BBC complaints procedure. 
[normal]How well has the BBC performed in the current charter period in achieving its mission and public purposes?[bold]1) Breaches of Editorial Guidelines on Accuracy:
[normal]Failures to meet Editorial Guidelines on accuracy are alarmingly common. Those failures appear in written, audio and filmed BBC content and increasingly on social media platforms used by BBC correspondents which, according to the BBC, are subject to the same editorial demands. 
[normal]Examples of inaccurate information promoted on social media include:
[normal]A false 
[normal]claim of an Israeli air raid
[normal] on Gaza on 19/11/13.
[normal] 
[normal]The 
[normal]misrepresentation of a picture
[normal] from the conflict in Syria as having been taken in the Gaza Strip.
[normal]Inaccurate representation
[normal] of casualty figures.
[normal]Inaccurate representation
[normal] of cause of death of a Palestinian prisoner.
[normal]Examples of inaccurate information in BBC reports include:
